# ===========================================
# Notes
# ===========================================
#
# This .dockerignore file excludes files that are not needed
# in the Docker image to keep the image size small and secure.
#
# Key exclusions:
# 1. Development dependencies and tools
# 2. Source code (only built artifacts needed)
# 3. Documentation and configuration files
# 4. Test files and test results
# 5. IDE and OS specific files
# 6. Environment files (should be mounted or injected)
#
# The Docker build will copy the built application (dist/)
# and necessary configuration files only.
#
# ===========================================








